        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali116-kilavi">itu viṉaivalapāṅkiṟ ṟalaiviyai āṟṟiṭaik kaṇṭu vilakkiya talaivaṉōṭu avaḷ cilamoḻi kūṟik kuṟiyiṭaṅ kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"/>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali116">
                <l>pāṅkarum pāṭṭaṅkāṟ kaṉṟoṭu celvēmen </l>
                <l>tāmpi ṉorutalai paṟṟiṉai yīṅkemmai </l>
                <l>muṉṉainiṉ ṟāṅkē vilakkiya vellānī </l>
                <l>yeṉṉēmuṟ ṟāay viṭu; </l>
                <l rend="space">viṭēṉ, toṭīiya celvārt tumittetir maṇṭuṅ </l>
                <l>kaṭuvaya nākupō ṉōkkit toḻuvāyi  </l>
                <l>ṉīṅkic ciṉavuvāy maṟṟu; </l>
                <l rend="space">nīnīṅku, taṉkaṉṟu cērntārkaṭ kataviṟṟāc ceṉṟāṅku </l>
                <l>vaṉkaṇṇa ḷāyvara lōmpu; </l>
                <l rend="space">yāyvaruka voṉṟō piṟarvaruka maṟṟuniṉ </l>
                <l>kōvariṉu miṅkē varuka taḷarēṉyā </l>
                <l>ṉīyaruḷi nalkap peṟiṉ;</l>
                <l rend="space">niṉṉaiyāṉ colliṉavum pēṇāy niṉaiik </l>
                <l>kaṉaipeya lēṟṟiṟ ṟalaicāyt teṉaiyatūu </l>
                <l>māṟetir kūṟi mayakkup paṭukuvāy </l>
                <l>kalattoṭiyāñ celvuḻi nāṭip pulattum </l>
                <l>varuvaiyā ṉāṇili nī.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l corresp="3">Hey you who blocked [our way] there, standing in front</l>
                <l corresp="2">of us here, being one who gripped on one end the cattle rope</l>
                <l corresp="1">of us who were going with the calves at the time in the difficult [to reach] side garden,</l>
                <l corresp="4">what are you confused about? Let go!</l>
                <l>I won’t let go, Looking [at me] like a fierce strong she-buffalo </l>
                <l>who will cut off [and] rush against those who go [by] in order to get at [them],</l>
                <l corresp="5-7">leaving the door of the cattle stall you are angry.</l>
                <l>You leave: going like the cow that has given birth in anger at those who join her calf,</l>
                <l corresp="8-9">as she is strong, beware of coming [close].</l>
                <l>My mother may come for one, ah. Or else others may come.</l>
                <l>Even if you king came let him come. I won’t falter</l>
                <l corresp="10-12">if I can get you to graciously grant.</l>
                <l>You don’t pay heed to what I say to you. Thinking,</l>
                <l>bending [your] head like a bull in the intense rain, talking</l>
                <l>back with whatever answer you fall into confusion.</l>
                <l>Searching [us] when we go with the vessel you will come</l>
                <l corresp="13-17">to the field too. You are without shame.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
